President Obama announced his intent to nominate four individuals to key administration posts. The nominees are David Michaels for Assistant Secretary for the Occupational Safety and Health Administration, Benjamin B. Tucker for Deputy Director for State, Local and Tribal Affairs at the Office of National Drug Control Policy, Mary Jo Wills for Ambassador to the Republic of Mauritius and to the Republic of Seychelles, and David S. Ferriero for Archivist of the United States at the National Archives and Records Administration. Each nominee brings extensive expertise and experience in their respective fields.